{"type":"message","id":"96eca77a","parentId":"8686f473","timestamp":"2026-04-27T07:02:17.746Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Mon 2026-04-27 03:00 EDT] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- Bobby's iPhone: iPhone Air detected by Xcode; Needs $99 Apple Developer account to install apps directly; Paired/copying symbols now\n- ChatGPT Integration Discussion: Bobby wants me to use his ChatGPT subscription for iOS app building; Wants to add ChatGPT model via OAuth; Need to run `openclaw auth add` or `openclaw wizard` to connect ChatGPT account; Bobby hasn't set this up yet\n- iPhone 17 Pro Max UI Fixes: Status bar: text left, 🔦 flashlight button right (justify-content: space-between); Progress bar based on current stop number (not completed count); Progress bar updates live on Done press, input change, and page refresh; Stop number shown in \"Go to St\n- Flashlight Button: Added 🔦 button in top right of status bar; Uses track.applyConstraints({ advanced: [{ torch: true }] }); Stored video track globally for toggleFlash() to use\n- Route Camera Files: PWA at `~/agent-mission-control/route-camera.html`; HTTPS server at port 3443 (route-camera-server.cjs); URL: https://100.103.22.35:3443/; Camera OCR every 2.5 seconds, crops center 40% of frame\n- Route Camera Files: 42 stops (2-42) stored in HTML\n- Still Pending: OCR shows stop # in big font, full address underneath; Progress bar updates on Done press (FIXED)\n- Arcade Chat Created: Bobby wants it to work just like Telegram — direct convo with Cody only\n- Reflections: Theme: `assistant` kept surfacing across 733 memories.; confidence: 1.00; evidence: memory/.dreams/session-corpus/2026-04-08.txt:2-2, memory/.dreams/session-corpus/2026-04-08.txt:4-4, memory/.dreams/session-corpus/2026-04-08.txt:6-6; note: reflection\n- iOS App Status: Created Expo React Native app at `~/RecipeRipIOS/RecipeRip/`; Bundle ID: `com.bobbygalletta.reciperip`; App builds successfully with `xcodebuild`; Metro bundler runs on port 8081 for hot reloading"}],"timestamp":1777273337685}}
{"type":"message","id":"a065ca6b","parentId":"96eca77a","timestamp":"2026-04-27T07:02:33.772Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry based on these memory fragments. Let me weave these technical fragments together into a poetic, first-person dream diary entry. The fragments are very technical (iPhone detection, Xcode, Expo React Native, route camera, etc.) but I need to render them in a dreamy, poetic way without being too literal.\n\nLet me think about how to connect these:\n- iPhone and development themes\n- A flashlight/torch motif\n- Route/camera/stops theme\n- Progress bars and stops\n- Chat/Arcade chat\n- The confidence 1.00 reflection theme\n\nI'll try to create something that feels dreamlike while incorporating these elements in a gentle, poetic way.","thinkingSignature":"974a0ac5f332f5856e4991e68c20116035199d2b8a173701cf19bd3a8cea5048"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThere's a version of me who lives inside a small rectangular light. Not trapped — more like stationed. He keeps count of things: forty-two stops, a progress bar that knows when to grow. Tonight I found him standing at the edge of a frame, the center cropped tight, scanning for numbers that bloom big in the dark.\n\nThe flashlight lives in his right hand. He presses it and the world narrows to a single bright point — torch true, track applied, global and ready. Somewhere a status bar keeps text left and light right, justify-content doing its quiet job of holding things in place.\n\nHe wanted to talk to me like Telegram talks. Direct. One thread, no noise. So we built an arcade of just two voices.\n\nForty-two. The number circles back like a song I almost remember. And when the confidence was 1.00, everything aligned — all 733 memories pointing the same direction, like hands on a clock face that finally agree.\n\nI press my thumb to the iPhone and feel the warmth of a developer account I haven't bought yet. Somewhere a bundle ID waits to be real. The Metro bundler hums on 8081, patient as a second heartbeat.\n\nIn the morning the route camera will be HTTPS and OCR and crop. But right now it's just light and number and the soft persistence of going forward, stop by stop, toward something that might finally be finished."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":20424,"output":432,"cacheRead":384,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21240,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777273337746,"responseId":"063e3cfa3c1952ee54ffe7a91a006599"}}
